<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="jn0a19a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="jn0" href="#jn0a19">JN0: </a>  <a href="../../ff/unbs/jn0all.htm#jn0a19a"> (Cornell) appendix 19(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> [Scene: draughty little stone-flagged room, chest of drawers to left, on which are the remains of lunch, in the centre, a small table on which are <i>writing materials</i> (<i>He</i> never forgot them) and a saltcellar: in the background, a small-sized bed. A young man with a snivelling nose sits at the little table: on the bed sit a madonna and plaintive infant. It is a January day.] Title of above: <cite>The Anarchist</cite>. </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: This final, no doubt most truthful, epiphany was included in a letter to Stanislaus Joyce postmarked 10 January 1907 when Joyce was working as a bank clerk in Rome. The original is in Cornell. </mm> </dd></dl>
